# normix Project Overview

## Purpose

`normix` is a JAX package implementing Generalized Hyperbolic distributions and related distributions as exponential families. Built on Equinox for immutable pytree modules.

## Design Philosophy

- **Minimalist:** no redundant methods, wrappers, or variables. One canonical representation per concept.
- **Immutable:** all distributions are `eqx.Module` pytrees. No mutation, no caching, no `_fitted` flags. M-step returns a new model.
- **Autodiff-first:** `expectation_params`, `fisher_information`, and gradients derived from `jax.grad`/`jax.hessian` on `_log_partition_from_theta`. No separate analytical overrides unless registered via `custom_jvp`.
- **Unbatched core:** `_log_prob` and `_sample` operate on single observations. Batching via `jax.vmap` or `jnp.vectorize`.
- **Separation of concerns:** model knows math (E-step, M-step); fitter knows iteration (convergence, scheduling).

## Dependencies

`jax`, `equinox`, `jaxopt`, `tensorflow_probability.substrates.jax` (Bessel only), `optax` (optional).

## Key Architecture

- `ExponentialFamily(eqx.Module)` — base class; subclass implements `_log_partition_from_theta`, `natural_params`, `sufficient_statistics`, `log_base_measure`
- `JointNormalMixture(ExponentialFamily)` — joint $f(x,y)$ for normal-subordinator mixtures
- `NormalMixture(eqx.Module)` — marginal $f(x) = \int f(x,y) dy$; owns a `JointNormalMixture`
- `BatchEMFitter` / `OnlineEMFitter` / `MiniBatchEMFitter` — fitter classes separate from model

## Distributions

| Distribution | Subordinator | Stored Attributes |
|---|---|---|
| Gamma | — | `alpha`, `beta` |
| InverseGamma | — | `alpha`, `beta` |
| InverseGaussian | — | `mu`, `lam` |
| GIG | — | `p`, `a`, `b` |
| MultivariateNormal | — | `mu`, `L` (Cholesky) |
| VarianceGamma | Gamma | `mu`, `gamma`, `L`, `alpha`, `beta` |
| NormalInverseGamma | InverseGamma | `mu`, `gamma`, `L`, `alpha`, `beta` |
| NormalInverseGaussian | InverseGaussian | `mu`, `gamma`, `L`, `delta`, `eta` |
| GeneralizedHyperbolic | GIG | `mu`, `gamma`, `L`, `p`, `a`, `b` |

## Bessel Functions (`_bessel.py`)

`log_kv(v, z)` with `@jax.custom_jvp`: TFP evaluation, exact ∂/∂z via recurrence, analytical ∂/∂ν via DLMF 10.40.2 for large z, finite differences otherwise.

## GIG η→θ

η-rescaling ($s = \sqrt{\eta_2/\eta_3}$) before `jaxopt.LBFGSB` solve. See `docs/jax_design.md`.

